```json
{
  "translations": [
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b1",
      "translation": "Our high-quality, recurring profit sources and active management of in-force policies drove after-tax operating profit growth of 5% to $5.942 billion,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b2",
      "translation": "and maintained the operating profit margin at 16.9%. Renewal premiums collected increased 10%, with recurring premiums representing 90% of total premiums collected in 2020 and"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b3",
      "translation": "above. After-tax operating profit growth benefited from significant positive claims experience throughout the year, which offset the decline in returns on new fixed income investments and lower long-term equity return"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b4",
      "translation": "Overview\nFinancial and Operating Review\nCorporate Governance\nOther Information\nFinancial Statements"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b5",
      "translation": "investment returns. As expected, the exceptional positive medical claims experience reported in the first half did not recur in the second half, but we continued to see"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b6",
      "translation": "positive contributions from this source to after-tax operating profit growth. With AIA Thailand's lapse experience normalizing, renewal rates improved in the second half, with the Group's renewal rate at 95%."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b7",
      "translation": "improvement, and the Group's renewal rate was 95%."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b8",
      "translation": "Mainland China recorded strong growth, with after-tax operating profit increasing 14% for the year, primarily due to our growing in-force policy portfolio and favorable claims experience."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b9",
      "translation": "experience. Although the significant positive claims experience in the first half normalized in the second half, overall claims experience for the year remained positive."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b10",
      "translation": "Hong Kong's after-tax operating profit increased 10%, driven by business growth and favorable claims experience, which substantially offset the decline in investment returns from falling bond yields"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b11",
      "translation": "and the negative impact of lower long-term investment return assumptions since end-2019."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b12",
      "translation": "Thailand's after-tax operating profit decreased 7% for the year. Although lapse experience improved significantly in the second half, the decline in the Thai stock market and lower long-term equity return assumptions"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b13",
      "translation": "substantially offset positive operating experience and business growth."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b14",
      "translation": "Singapore's after-tax operating profit increased 8%, benefiting from in-force policy portfolio growth and improved operating experience in renewal rates, expenses, and claims."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b15",
      "translation": "Malaysia's after-tax operating profit remained broadly stable, as business growth and positive claims experience were offset by a one-time provision made for an industry initiative aimed at identifying and paying accumulated"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b16",
      "translation": "unreported death claims. Excluding this provision, Malaysia's after-tax operating profit increased"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b17",
      "translation": "8%."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b18",
      "translation": "Other markets' after-tax operating profit decreased 11%, with Australia's after-tax operating profit $68 million lower than 2019 levels, primarily due to lower"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b19",
      "translation": "yields on disability insurance policies. Growth in Taiwan and Vietnam was substantially offset by decreases in after-tax operating profit in Indonesia, the Philippines, and South Korea."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b20",
      "translation": "Average shareholders' equity increased 11% to $45.7 billion, with return on shareholders' equity of 13.0%."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p25_b21",
      "translation": "2020 Annual Report\n023"
    }
  ]
}
